  "title": "Accountant/Tech (Immediate/East)",
  "description": "<p><strong>hybrid working environment</strong><br /><strong>great culture</strong><br /><strong>APAC portfolio</strong><br /><br /><strong>about the company</strong><br />This company is a multi-billion MNC and has been on a steady growth since its inception. Having a long history that spans decades, they have anchored themselves to be a market leader. They are currently looking for a high calibre candidate to join the Team as an Accountant.</p><p><strong>about the job</strong><br />You'll be responsible for the full spectrum of bookkeeping and financial reporting. This includes daily recording of transactions, preparing accurate monthly and annual financial statements for an APAC portfolio. You will also manage taxation functions. </p><p><strong>skills and experience required</strong><br />You should ideally be degree qualified in accounting or an equivalent. You should have at least 5 years of experience in full sets of accounts. You are a strong communicator and work well independently. You will be reporting to the Finance Manager directly so you have to be dynamic and confident, able to engage stakeholders well.  Candidates with notice period of 2 months will not be considered. </p><p>To apply online please use the 'apply' function, (EA R22111662)</p>",
